D2C brand & consumer app, work with me: https://sfrance.co

 Get the file from the video: https://curiousmarketer.gumroad.com/l/programmatic-creative-testing

WATCH NEXT 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QDvuD90XV9k

TOOLS (affiliate links) 

Templated (Static ads image creation at scale):
https://swiy.co/templated

Icon (Turn your mini-VSL script into an ad):
https://swiy.co/icon

WORK WITH ME 
https://tally.so/r/wM4pRA

CONNECT WITH ME 

https://twitter.com/meetstef
https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephane-franceschini

DESCRIPTION:

Learn how to run programmatic creative testing for Facebook (Meta) Adsfast, logically, and at scale. This video shows a complete system that turns ad creative into variables (USP, marketing angle, messaging framework, level of awareness, market sophistication, copy length), feeds them to an LLM, and pushes bulk ads into Ads Managerso you can test more ideas, find winners, and iterate with intent.

What youll see:
 The thinking: segmenting an ad into controllable variables (USP  angles  frameworks  awareness/sophistication) so you test messages, not guesses.  
 The build: a Google Sheets + Make.com backend that composes prompts (ChatGPT/Claude), generates hooks, and creates static image ads from templates (via an image templating API).  
 The workflow: generate hooks  human review  render variants  push to existing ad sets  let the algorithm allocate spend  mark winners  iterate.  
 Expansion: turn winning hooks into mini VSL/text-based scripts for voiceover + B-roll assembly.  
 Example used: Jones Road Beautys Miracle Balm to illustrate USP  angle  hook  image  ad deployment.

Why this matters:
 Systematic creative coverage: test multiple USPs and angles without creative chaos.  
 Voice of customer first: mine reviews, forums, and Reddit for exact phrasing to feed the model.  
 Faster throughput: prioritize static images to validate hooks before producing video.  
 Structured iteration: once a winner emerges, spin variants (new images, adjacent angles, new frameworks) instead of starting from scratch.

Key concepts included:
 Unique Selling Proposition (USP) vs. marketing angles (angle = one focused way to express a USP).  
 Messaging frameworks (e.g., bold statements, desire/future state) and copy length control.  
 Eugene Schwartz: levels of awareness (unaware  most aware) and market sophistication (15).  
 Campaign structure approach: build campaigns/ad sets yourself, push ads via API, and give the algorithm wide room to optimize.

Tools/workflow stack:
 Research & prompts: Google Sheets (context hub), voice-of-customer gold nuggets (reviews, forums).  
 Automation: Make.com for prompt assembly + API calls.  
 LLMs: ChatGPT / Claude for copy generation.  
 Creatives: template-based image rendering via API (auto-fit headline length).  
 Ads Manager: bulk ad creation into selected ad sets.  
 Post-win: script generation for mini VSLs and B-roll mapping in an editor.

Who this is for:
 Media buyers, performance marketers, founders, agencies, and teams running ecom, SaaS, apps, or services on Meta who want faster, more logical creative testing and a repeatable system.

Search intents this video answers:
 How to test Facebook ads fast  
 Facebook ads creative testing framework  
 Programmatic creative testing Meta ads  
 AI for Facebook ads copy + image generation  
 Bulk ad creation Google Sheets + Make.com

TIMESTAMPS:

00:00 - Introduction to programmatic testing
04:45 - Mental framework overview
09:31 - Context: brand, product, voice
14:16 - System setup: sheets, automations
19:02 - Unique selling propositions and angles
23:47 - Hooks, frameworks, awareness
28:33 - From hooks to images and ads
33:18 - Iteration, scripts, and wrap-up
